So I was nominated to do this 10 facts about me thing(?) by @gravityy_z and I'm not keen on it, but whatever, here goes.
•I'm 27 years old going on 28 here in a few more days(October 7th(send me something (I'm lonely 😂)))
•I live alone here in Virginia and I'm currently getting my house remodeled (should see the bathroom. It's paradise).
•I spent 6 years of my life as a United States Marine with the MOSs' of 7011 and a 3112.
•This picture was taken when I was stationed in Japan. It took place during Valentine's day. I didn't have a date, but the place I was invited to was a "dress to impress" place, so I wore what I had(the suit was what I wore to my highschool prom😂)
•I got into gaming at a very young age, but I didn't start the competitive scene until late Halo 2. My team and I(John, Stephen, Travis) did Halo 3 competitively and we ended up in 47th out of thousands of teams. Top 50 is impressive in my eyes. When Bungie gave Halo over to 343 I was kinda disappointed. Then Destiny came into the picture and here I am now.
•I love to travel. I've been all over the US, I've been to Japan, Australia, Philippines, Thailand, Italy, and other places. I'm planning a trip to Vegas and Greece soon.
•I love to read and write. I've never published anything, but I do have a few fantasy-related stories that I'm proud of.
•I'm currently a bartender and it's a fun job. I enjoy it.
•Sometimes I can be a little too hype(if you haven't watched my streams/posts😂). I just like to see others laugh and to be happy.
•Team Enigma would not have happened if I didn't meet @chuchigaming or @lonexwolflegend in a Destiny Facebook community group. Thank you Wolf for giving me the opportunity to show you my potential and thank you Chuchi for sticking around and remaining loyal through all the bumps.🌹

People have been speculating that there will be a complete new map with the release of season 11 and the season 10 event being this week but there's this structure being built right now surely it cannot be built in less than 2 weeks. If it did there would be no point since there would be a new map anyways. Why would fortnite put their time to make this if there will be a complete new map in 2 weeks? This leads me to expect we will have the same map but obviously with altered POI's and new ones too, although you could argue they will bring a new map because they are bringing back old loved POI's (Dusty Depot, OG Factories, Greasy Grove etc.) to bring back good memories we had then wheen we really enjoyed fortnite. Its to try give us the same vibes as we did in season 1,2,3 although it dosent work with some of the things in the game which is why so many people got bored and left the game. I will agree fortnite needs a new start by introducing a new map, but with this happening I don't think it will. This just a theory by me and also remember the gotham city/Batman event is ending soon so complete your challenges whilst you can!

Wer sind wir ? - Wir sind 4 Leute unterschiedlichen Alters und kommen aus den unterschiedlichsten Teilen Deutschlands. Kennengelernt haben wir uns über den Gaming-Clan "Simu-Firefighters", in welchem wir früher als Admins tätig waren. Aus Zeitlichen und Beruflichen Gründen sind wir dort aber nicht mehr tätig. 
Allerdings wollten wir auf das Gaming nicht verzichten und treffen und jetzt ab und zu zum zocken. 
Wieso gibt es diese Seite ? - Wie schon erwähnt zocken wir ab und zu. Und daran wollen wir euch teilhaben lassen. In dem wir hier Bilder Posten zudem werden wir Livestreams auf Twitch übertragen. Um euch über unsere Streams zu informieren gibt es diese Seite. 
In den nächsten Wochen füllen wir dann alle unsere Seiten mit Inhalten. 
Wir hoffen ihr teilt unsere Seite fleissig , damit die Community stetig wächst.

preview_comments.text: I’m all for a power-up magnet! Awesome idea Heffie6! 😃

caption.text:
September 2019 Runner of the Month - Heffie6!
.
If Heffie6 had an opportunity to choose any new skill or boost for her character, she would choose a power-up magnet. “Her co-ordination is still not brilliant,” she says. Therefore, she would like to attract the chests and power-ups so she doesn’t have to jump. That’s what Heffie6 told Imangi at first, then she responded back a day later saying she gave it more thought and she had a better idea for a runner’s skill. This is why we adore Heffie6, and the reason why she’s this month’s Runner of the Month. She went back to the drawing board and thought of even more ideas. “Telepathy,” she said. It’s useful when you need to run 5 times in the tunnel, but keep getting waterslides. It would let you know if you needed to go left or right. The power-up magnet and the telepathy both sound like amazing ideas for Temple Run 2!
. 
This Temple Run tip is brought to you by Heffie6, “Don’t trip! The Demon Monkey will always get you!” That’s the truth! Thanks Heffie6 for being a fan of Temple Run!
Working on something new in @oldschool.runescape. Will have a stats update tomorrow to show my progress so far. #osrs #gaming
